casebody.data:
WILLIAMS BROTHERS CORPORATION and ZURICH GENERAL ACCIDENT and LIABILITY INSURANCE COMPANY, LTD., v. RUFUS McAMY HICKS and EMPIRE A. HICKS, his wife, and FLORIDA INDUSTRIAL COMMISSION. 16 So. (2nd) 432

January Term, 1944

February 1, 1944 Division B Rehearing Denied February 15, 1944 McKay, Dixon & DeJarnette and A. Lee Bradford, for appellants. Cody Fowler, for appellees. PER CURIAM:

Judgment affirmed.

Additional attorney’s fee in the sum of $150.00 for services in circuit and Supreme Court to be recovered by appel-lees from appellants is awarded.

So ordered.

BUFORD, C. J., BROWN, THOMAS and SEBRING, JJ., concur.
